sentences: William Ackerman (born November 16, 1949) is an American guitarist and record producer who founded Windham Hill Records.
Early years =
In 1972, he founded Windham Hill Builders in Palo Alto while playing music for Stanford theater productions and performing impromptu concerts in town.
The second album he released in 1976 was by his cousin, guitarist  Alex De Grassi, followed by one in 1977 by his guitar teacher, Robbie Basho.

He left carpentry to pursue music full time in 1980.

Autumn was a solo piano album that helped define the genre of relaxing, acoustic music that Ackerman had been creating at Windham Hill.
In 1982, A&M Records became Windham Hill's distributor.
By 1984, Ackerman no longer wanted to run a large corporation.
